{"version": "2.0","name": "aDBstract","subline": "OOP Database made real","username": "SelfDevel","created": "03/10/2011","website": "http://yoantonioroldan.esy.es/","update": "03/19/2016","update_today": true,"email": "antonio_irp@hotmail.com","description": "aDBstract will provide Object Oriented Programming to your database. ","intro": "Hi, thank you for purchasing this item. This item will save you tons of time, this tool will abstract you from your database, you only have to create a new object and run the execute insert, update, select or delete method from the database controller. This tool is intended to full OOP your database.","button_1_text": "Installation","button_2_text": "Run aDBstract","button_3_text": "How to use","button_1_url": "#installation","button_2_url": "#run_adbstract","button_3_url": "#how_to_use","sections": [{"title": "Installation","id": "installation","content": "<p>\tYou will only have to need the following:</p>\n<ol>\n\t<li>\t\tExtract the content from aDBstract folder into your public html folder&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li>\t\tOpen aDBstract/com/selfdeve/adbstract/ConnectionManager.php</li>\n\t<li>\t\tConfigure your own access database parameters, make sure they are valid</li>\n\t<li>\t\tPower On your locals servers, apache and mysql</li>\n\t<li>\t\tEnter the following url in your browser:&nbsp;http://localhost/aDBstract/WebContent/index.php</li>\n\t<li>\t\tYou must see the aDBstract index page</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\t<a href=\"http://s9.postimg.org/g2k5xagan/index_page.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://s9.postimg.org/g2k5xagan/index_page.jpg\"></a></p>\n<p>\t&nbsp;</p>\n"},{"title": "Run aDBstract","id": "run_adbstract","content": "<p>\tFollow these steps to create the database Bean Class and Controller Class:</p>\n<ol>\n\t<li>\t\tClick the Get tables button</li>\n\t<li>\t\tSelect the table &nbsp;that you want to abstract for.</li>\n\t<li>\t\tSet the class name if you want, by default Bean.php and Controller.php files will be created.</li>\n\t<li>\t\tClick the Run aDBstract! button</li>\n\t<li>\t\tCheck the GeneratedClases folder, now you can export the files.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\t<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://s16.postimg.org/v2wrx7bw5/how_to_use.jpg\"></p>\n"},{"title": "How to use","id": "how_to_use","content": "<p>\tFollow thes steps to use the aDBstract generated clases:</p>\n<ol>\n\t<li>\t\tInitalize a PDO object: $pdo = new PDO(&quot;my conn params&quot;, &quot;myuser&quot;, &quot;mypassword&quot;);</li>\n\t<li>\t\tInitialize a new Object of the database Controller class: $controller = new Controller($pdo);</li>\n\t<li>\t\tInitializa some new Object of the database Bean class: $bean = new Bean();</li>\n\t<li>\t\tSet data to the Bean Object: $bean-&gt;setField1(&quot;data&quot;); $bean-&gt;setField7(&quot;data7&quot;);</li>\n\t<li>\t\tRun the Controller method you want: &nbsp;$controller-&gt;executeSelect($bean);</li>\n\t<li>\t\tRead the returned data from your database</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\t<li>\t\texecuteSelect method: returns an array of Bean Object.</li>\n\t<li>\t\texecuteInsert method: returns the number of inserted rows.</li>\n\t<li>\t\texecuteUpdate method: returns the number of affected rows.</li>\n\t<li>\t\texecuteDelete method: returns the number of deleted rows.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\tCheck the <a href=\"#options\">#options</a>&nbsp; section to extend the functionality features</p>\n<p>\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\t&nbsp;</p>\n"},{"title": "Options","id": "options","content": "<p>\tYou can use the followings options:</p>\n<ul>\t<li>\t\tLIMIT clause</li>\n\t<li>\t\tOFFSET clause</li>\n\t<li>\t\tORDER by clause</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\t&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n\t<li>\t\tUsing ORDER BY clause:</li>\n</ol>\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n\t<li>\t\tSet $controller-&gt;setOrderBy($array), $array must be an array like:</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 120px;\">\n\t$array = [</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 160px;\">\n\t&quot;myField1Name&quot;: &quot;ASC&quot;,</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 160px;\">\n\t&quot;myField4Name&quot;: &quot;DESC&quot;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 120px;\">\n\t]</p>\n<ul>\t<li style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n\t\tRun your select query</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n\t2.- Using LIMIT and OFFSET:</p>\n<ul>\t<li style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n\t\tSet $controller-&gt;setLimit($int), $int is an integer number representing the LIMIT clause value</li>\n\t<li style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n\t\tYou can optionally set a OFFSET clause if you want: $controller-&gt;setOffset($offst), $offst is an integer representing the OFFSET clause value.</li>\n</ul>\n"}],"use_sub": false,"logo": "","favicon": "","customcss": "","easing": "swing","easingduration": "500","bgimage": "","bgrepeat": "repeat","bgattachment": "scroll","bgcolor": "EDF6EE","textcolor": "412E28","linkcolor": "B3204D","hrcolor1": "DBE3DC","hrcolor2": "F6FFF7","btncolor": "FFFFFF","btncolor1": "B3204D","btncolor2": "7D1636","sidebarbgimage": "","sidebarbgrepeat": "repeat","sidebarbgcolor": "261F02","sidebartextcolor": "EDF6EE","sidebarlinkcolor": "EDF6EE","sidebaractivecolor": "2B2302","sidebaractivetextcolor": "B3204D","sidebarhrcolor1": "0F0C01","sidebarhrcolor2": "382E03","cufon": "","documentationttype": "bootstrap","itemURL": "","sendJSON": "","sendZIP": "","sendPWD": "","cke_629_uiElement": false,"cke_632_uiElement": false,"cke_636_uiElement": false,"cke_639_uiElement": false,"cke_643_uiElement": false,"cke_646_uiElement": false,"cke_650_uiElement": false,"cke_653_uiElement": false}